{{Quote|All right, but I'm out of credits, so it's Republic Senate rules. That's where we waste a lot of time trading cards and trying to beat each other, but in the end nobody wins, everybody loses, and nobody accomplishes anything. It's like stalemate, except the goal is to pass time until the audience gets bored and leaves.|[[Atton Rand]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>}}
'''Republic Senate rules''' was a gameplay style of [[Pazaak/Legends|pazaak]]. It drew its name from the bureaucratic nature of the rules of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]]. Under Republic Senate rules, the goal was simply to pass the time; nothing was bet, and no one came out on top.

